desc:
Waiting on: [https://trello.com/c/7g9Wio0y/2359-change-requests-incorporate-visit-columns-into-idx-etl-appointment-table](https://trello.com/c/7g9Wio0y/2359-change-requests-incorporate-visit-columns-into-idx-etl-appointment-table "smartCard-inline")

In order to

1. establish integrity of DMAR’s primary patient database, and
2. optimize query time for the most critical of DMAR’s user-facing workflows,

all foreign key records should be fully populated with the accompanying data, such as visit\_status and last\_name. For example, a complete system ensures that when a process queries a row from pocdart2.demographics, it can be sure that the patient name from IDX is associated. The timing of Sheppard Pratt’s HL7 workflows (SIU) have historically required temporary placeholders (`populate_foreign_key()`) with the expectation that IDX will also activate the workflows (ADT) for the associated visit/pt shortly thereafter to populate associated tables. This transitional state we call “ghost records.” Ghost records are defined as:

```
mysql> select count(*) from visits where mrn is NULL;
+----------+
| count(*) |
+----------+
|    15546 |
+----------+
1 row in set (0.00 sec)

mysql> select count(*) from demographics where first_name is null;
+----------+
| count(*) |
+----------+
|     6686 |
+----------+
1 row in set (0.02 sec)
```

Resolution of one such workflow was deployed to the IDX HL7 client in June 2023. Identifying any workflows still actively creating these records requires a one-time cleaning so we can isolate and evaluate them. Resolution means either:

1. Populating all relevant columns associated with that ghost record, or
2. Deleting the ghost record entirely from the database

desc:
As part of the V2 deployment, there are planned changes to the Proxy project to add parent-proxy measures that are currently used for patients under the age of 12 years. Parent-proxy measures will be available only using the proxy PROM buttons and outcomes section. In addition, the patient PROMs for pediatric will lower the minimum age to 8 to match the official minimum age used by HealthMeasures.

Site managers were informed of these changes on Friday, 12/2 but drew concerns from Robert who stated he was not aware of these changes being part of the V2 deployment and was concerned that user fidelity would drop as a result of these changes (for Community in particular as users would have to engage with the proxy PROM system for the first time). Feedback from Community site managers thus far do not indicate any major concerns about the changes. Proxy PROMs may be added on the project level to account for continued parent-proxy reporting consistency for younger patients.

This card was created to represent any work related to communication with users about the V2 changes, as well as completing a post-mortem about how communication about these project changes got lost over the course of the last few months of the deployment process.

As a Quality team member, I was to interact with the Tableau dashboard to help audit PRN medication follow up on inpatient units that accounts for the updated workflow. To enable this, a dashboard should be set-up using the data from the SCM test environment because the new workflow has been activated there but it has not yet been implemented in production SCM.

**DoD:** A version of the PRN dashboard that uses data staged from the SCM test environment with the new PRN workflow has been published to Tableau Server for validation and feedback.

from Geoff B:

We have been working to have a follow-up task generated with all given PRNs in Sunrise. This will alter how we look for PRN follow-ups on the dashboard. I have attached an info sheet outlying some things that will now happen.

Basically, the trigger of giving a PRN creates a PRN follow-up order. That order shows as a task on the MAR for the users to complete.

This is currently active in TEST, but we are still finalizing what PRN follow-up task we will use. Currently, it is assigned to the same task form as the Pain Medications.

desc:
0 patients have received an incorrect PROM due to survey sendout workflow  failing before the email is scheduled. 83 REDCap records that are currently compromised - send\_adm\_prom has been disable until the issue is resolved

REDCap fields `visit_number_backup` and `survey_id` currently corrupted. Data in these fields propagate to other systems if a patient has completed a survey.

Only 1 record ([record 15](https://sphsoutcomes.net/redcap/redcap_v14.0.1/DataExport/index.php?pid=349&report_id=1534 "‌")) has completed PROM data that needs to be cleaned up across the system due to the propagation errors.

Steps to resolve are:

1. fix redcap
2. re-enable send\_adm\_prom and omit from job_processor
3. clean up records in system (record 15)

‌

Breakdown of the 83 affected records:
\- 46 were created in REDCap but failed before they were sent out
\- 37 were sent, of which:
\--- 10 expired
\--- 27 still open, of which:
\------ 1 was taken

‌

[https://github.com/splresearch/pocdart\_cron\_scripts/pull/18/files](https://github.com/splresearch/pocdart_cron_scripts/pull/18/files "‌")
name: UNPLANNED WORK - Survey to patient map integrity

desc:
10/25: Mosaic program manager Kylie Hall and therapist Kayleigh Weaver report that patient MRN 00000981 (C. Malstrom) appeared on the dashboard with an ‘enroll’ status despite completing PROMs previously. Patient completed an admission PROM on 10/25 during the appointment.

10/25-10/26: Amber and Jacqui review community REDCap to find all records associated with the patient MRN and name. Only 1 [record](https://sheppardpratt.healthcare/redcap/redcap_v13.10.4/DataEntry/record_home.php?pid=19&id=3790&arm=1 "‌") is found, associated with the admission PROM completed on 10/25.

10/27: Kylie Hall confirms that the patient has been admitted to Timonium location with Kayleigh as the primary therapist since 2021.

11/8: Kayleigh states that the PROMs were previously completed sometime in September 2023 and a custom PROM was added. She states that the patient confirmed completing them before 10/25:

“_Yes I did this most recently (prior to the deletion) probably the beginning/mid September.  I remember that I did it because I was adding a new PROM- one that is out of the automatic ones. I also asked the client if we had done them before and she also agreed. I added the borderline symptom list. And I did it through the webpage of DMAR. The client would usually do the assessments during the session.  Yes the completed scores would appear on the Hub. She said she never got any emails/texts prior to 10/25_”

Jacqui reviewed both Community REDCap projects for this patient and found that the patient was marked as ‘exempt’ until 10/25/2023. The first PROM notification sent to the patient was on 10/25/2023.  An email has been associated with this patient since 8/20/2022; a cell was added on 2/14/2023. There are no records of this patient completing PROMs before 10/25 in REDCap
name: UNPLANNED WORK - Missing completed PROMs for Mosaic patient

desc:
On 10/9 at 9:24:42 PM, the community hl7-receiver\_adt container encountered errors forwarding traffic to the hl7-receiver\_pocdart2 container, cutting off the pocdart2 database from receiving new data.

Restarting the adt container cleared this error:

```
connect EADDRNOTAVAIL 23.23.131.255:8890 - Local (0.0.0.0:0)
```

‌

Cannot read property 'event' of undefined was triggered 151 times, which probably caused the timeout. Manual messages resent using /home/ajm/scripts/resend_hl7.sh encountered the same error. Manual messages copied to and send from /home/ajm/simple-hl7/ did not fail.

**DoD**: a dedicated ingestion dashboard is sending its own messages to kw-next-gen adt receiver in community and the relay is disabled
name: UNPLANNED WORK - Community hl7-receiver message forwarding disconnected

desc:

Maintenance window: 9pm-12am

Documentation:

- OS: [pocdart.org/node/66](http://pocdart.org/node/66 "‌")
- Drupal: [http://pocdart.org/node/67](http://pocdart.org/node/67 "‌")

- Server Architecture: [https://lucid.app/lucidchart/3e24bdd0-1485-4255-a446-15538c1c363f/edit?page=0_0#](https://lucid.app/lucidchart/3e24bdd0-1485-4255-a446-15538c1c363f/edit?page=0_0# "‌")

Notes on REDCap configuration check: Read all suggestions carefully. Some explicitly note that they are inaccurate if the server has been recently restarted. All suggestions related to query\_cache can be ignored; we do not have query\_cache enabled and past research suggests it is deprecated.

Reboots should always be issued regardless whether or not apt requires it. This resets memory usage and applies changes so we can recover using a recent backup rather than being surprised by it during the next maintenance card.
name: Software Maintenance - October '23

desc:
Card to mark discussion w/ Alex & Matt regarding SharedInbox.

$290/year on the annual Starter plan gets us the following:

- 5000 inbound messages/month
- No storage limit
- Custom signature for replies

7-day trial and sandbox to test functionality

[https://sharedinbox.co/reply-to-emails-from-slack/](https://sharedinbox.co/reply-to-emails-from-slack/ "smartCard-inline")

Meeting with Alex went well, the Sandbox is promising save for a couple of issues. Viewing emails assigned to you only allows you to see emails that are due within the week or are overdue, and there was no visible way to configure automatic statuses or due dates. A ticket is being submitted via the Contact Us page in regards to that functionality. If this functionality exists or will be implemented by the devs, this is looking like a great replacement for MailClark.
name: SharedInbox Slack Integration

desc:
On 2024-01-03, cybereason’s cbram service caused a memory overload, slowing the Towson production server (sp-dmaras1) such that developers could not connect via SSH. To our knowledge, it was resolved before it affected the users. cbram started last night after a reboot; this has happened before and while we disabled `cybereason-sensor.service` last time, we did not disable `cbram.service`

Fix: kill cbram process from dev with ssh commands, logged into sp-dmaras1 to disable the service (which is separate from cybereason.service).

Details and commands are in the slack thread:

[https://splresearch.slack.com/archives/C02CMG7PJ5U/p1704292378420599](https://splresearch.slack.com/archives/C02CMG7PJ5U/p1704292378420599 "smartCard-inline")
name: Cybereason server overload 2023-01-03
